<span class="t s6" style="left:58px;bottom:212px;letter-spacing:0.15px;word-spacing:0.05px;">the meeting to answer questions and discuss any matters of concern. </span>
<span class="t s7" style="left:295px;bottom:859px;letter-spacing:-0.18px;">Speaker: Martin Orkin </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:806px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">A fascinating talk about the early years of The </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:774px;letter-spacing:0.19px;">Beatles and how they got started on the road </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:743px;letter-spacing:0.19px;">to amazing success! Our guest speaker Martin </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:711px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">Orkin will discuss this wonderful group, who </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:679px;letter-spacing:0.19px;">made so many fantastic recordings during the </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:647px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">era of Beatlemania: 'Love Me Do', 'She Loves </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:615px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">You', 'I Want To Hold Your Hand', 'A Hard Day's </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:583px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">Night', 'Help!', 'Day Tripper' and 'We Can Work </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:552px;letter-spacing:0.16px;">It Out'. </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:498px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">We will hear snippets of each of these great </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:467px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">records and many more, as Martin tells their </span>
<span class="t s1" style="left:295px;bottom:435px;letter-spacing:0.18px;">story. </span></div>

</section>

