<span class="t sj" style="left:33px;bottom:1021px;letter-spacing:0.08px;word-spacing:0.18px;">in a large park, the Great Park, on the eastern side of </span>
<span class="t sj" data-mappings='[[3,"fi"]]' style="left:33px;bottom:993px;letter-spacing:0.12px;word-spacing:0.01px;">Hatﬁeld, Hertfordshire, England. </span>
<span class="t sj" style="left:33px;bottom:966px;letter-spacing:0.13px;word-spacing:0.18px;">The present Jacobean house, a leading example of </span>
<span class="t sj" style="left:33px;bottom:937px;letter-spacing:0.1px;word-spacing:0.18px;">the prodigy house, was built in 1611 by Robert Cecil, 1st Earl of Salisbury and Chief </span>
<span class="t sj" style="left:33px;bottom:910px;letter-spacing:0.08px;word-spacing:0.22px;">Minister to James I. </span><span class="t sj" data-mappings='[[3,"fi"]]' style="left:235px;bottom:910px;letter-spacing:0.05px;word-spacing:0.23px;">Hatﬁeld's connection to Elizabeth I, however, holds the greatest </span>
<span class="t sj" style="left:33px;bottom:882px;letter-spacing:0.09px;word-spacing:0.19px;">fascination for visitors. The Rainbow Portrait and The Ermine Portrait of Elizabeth are </span>
<span class="t sj" style="left:33px;bottom:854px;letter-spacing:0.12px;word-spacing:0.13px;">in the main house, along with her hat, gloves, and a pair of her silk stockings, thought </span>
<span class="t sj" data-mappings='[[10,"fi"]]' style="left:33px;bottom:826px;letter-spacing:0.11px;word-spacing:0.17px;">to be the ﬁrst hosiery of its kind in England. </span>
